### ===========================================
### SmartWater Backend API Test
### Usage: Execute requests in order
### ===========================================

### 1. Login - Token will be saved automatically
# @name login
POST http://localhost:8080/api/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "bitebyte4@gmail.com",
  "password": "111111"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("auth_token", response.body.token);
    client.log("Token saved successfully!");
%}

### 2. Sensor Data (Public endpoint, no auth required)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/sensor/device/WATER_001/latest

### 3. Alert Evaluation (Uses saved token)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/alerts/evaluate
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

{
  "ph": 5.2,
  "temperature": 35,
  "turbidity": 8
}

### 4. Create Community Post (Uses saved token)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/community/posts
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

{
  "content": "Water quality report: Excellent conditions today!",
  "location": "City Lake"
}

### 5. Get Community Posts List
GET http://localhost:8080/api/community/posts?page=0&size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

### 6. Get User Alert History
GET http://localhost:8080/api/alerts/me
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

### 7. Get User Profile
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/me/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}
